{"type":"message","id":"c51c49ff","parentId":"c929f222","timestamp":"2026-03-22T18:32:37.531Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see there's a `providers/vllm.md` doc. Let me read that and also check the `providers/index.md` to understand how OpenClaw talks to external LLMs. Also let me check the `gateway/openai-http-api.md` since vLLM exposes an OpenAI-compatible API.","thinkingSignature":"ff5d59aad97a8a1120bc5c0b057ba1b62e9fa4794e5baa29947d82d6bc5b88de"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_79f7lmtr928a_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\providers\\vllm.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":29194,"output":114,"cacheRead":12352,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":41660,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774204352012}}
{"type":"message","id":"56226ba8","parentId":"c51c49ff","timestamp":"2026-03-22T18:32:37.546Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_79f7lmtr928a_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nsummary: \"Run OpenClaw with vLLM (OpenAI-compatible local server)\"\nread_when:\n  - You want to run OpenClaw against a local vLLM server\n  - You want OpenAI-compatible /v1 endpoints with your own models\ntitle: \"vLLM\"\n---\n\n# vLLM\n\nvLLM can serve open-source (and some custom) models via an **OpenAI-compatible** HTTP API. OpenClaw can connect to vLLM using the `openai-completions` API.\n\nOpenClaw can also **auto-discover** available models from vLLM when you opt in with `VLLM_API_KEY` (any value works if your server doesn’t enforce auth) and you do not define an explicit `models.providers.vllm` entry.\n\n## Quick start\n\n1. Start vLLM with an OpenAI-compatible server.\n\nYour base URL should expose `/v1` endpoints (e.g. `/v1/models`, `/v1/chat/completions`). vLLM commonly runs on:\n\n- `http://127.0.0.1:8000/v1`\n\n2. Opt in (any value works if no auth is configured):\n\n```bash\nexport VLLM_API_KEY=\"vllm-local\"\n```\n\n3. Select a model (replace with one of your vLLM model IDs):\n\n```json5\n{\n  agents: {\n    defaults: {\n      model: { primary: \"vllm/your-model-id\" },\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\n## Model discovery (implicit provider)\n\nWhen `VLLM_API_KEY` is set (or an auth profile exists) and you **do not** define `models.providers.vllm`, OpenClaw will query:\n\n- `GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/v1/models`\n\n…and convert the returned IDs into model entries.\n\nIf you set `models.providers.vllm` explicitly, auto-discovery is skipped and you must define models manually.\n\n## Explicit configuration (manual models)\n\nUse explicit config when:\n\n- vLLM runs on a different host/port.\n- You want to pin `contextWindow`/`maxTokens` values.\n- Your server requires a real API key (or you want to control headers).\n\n```json5\n{\n  models: {\n    providers: {\n      vllm: {\n        baseUrl: \"http://127.0.0.1:8000/v1\",\n        apiKey: \"${VLLM_API_KEY}\",\n        api: \"openai-completions\",\n        models: [\n          {\n            id: \"your-model-id\",\n            name: \"Local vLLM Model\",\n            reasoning: false,\n            input: [\"text\"],\n            cost: { input: 0, output: 0, cacheRead: 0, cacheWrite: 0 },\n            contextWindow: 128000,\n            maxTokens: 8192,\n          },\n        ],\n      },\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\n## Troubleshooting\n\n- Check the server is reachable:\n\n```bash\ncurl http://127.0.0.1:8000/v1/models\n```\n\n- If requests fail with auth errors, set a real `VLLM_API_KEY` that matches your server configuration, or configure the provider explicitly under `models.providers.vllm`.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774204357542}}
{"type":"message","id":"60a8230d","parentId":"56226ba8","timestamp":"2026-03-22T18:32:45.187Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So OpenClaw can connect to a vLLM server using the OpenAI-compatible API. The key thing I need is:\n\n1. A Paperspace machine running vLLM with the Qwen model\n2. Expose it via a public URL (or at least accessible)\n\nBut the issue is: I don't have a way to create a Paperspace machine via API without the proper CLI or knowing the exact API endpoints. Let me check if there's a way to do this with the Paperspace API.\n\nLet me look at the Paperspace API docs to figure out how to create a machine/notebook. Let me try the `paperspace-python` GitHub repo or check for common Paperspace API patterns.\n\nActually, thinking about this more practically — let me see if I can:","thinkingSignature":"9e63cb4f93bc9d525e7a189fa8a3d60912c1d1cc52b687f4542b18adc9283b7d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_c59851amardv_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"$headers = @{ \"Authorization\" = \"Bearer 131e4cbc99405a0e3af9710cc1607c\"; \"Content-Type\" = \"application/json\" }; Invoke-RestMethod -Uri \"https://api.paperspace.com/v1/users/me\" -Method GET -Headers $headers | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 5","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":30013,"output":268,"cacheRead":12352,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":42633,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774204357547}}
