{"type":"message","id":"73574067","parentId":"ed499ecf","timestamp":"2026-03-22T18:34:29.656Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_sl9qksuy5i6n_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Usage: paperspace-python machines availability [OPTIONS]\r\n\r\n  Get machine availability for the given region and machine type. Note:\r\n  availability is only provided for the dedicated GPU machine types. Also, not\r\n  all machine types are available in all regions\r\n\r\nOptions:\r\n  --region [ca1|ny2|ams1]         Name of the region  [required]\r\n  --machineType [Air|Standard|Pro|Advanced|GPU+|P4000|P5000|P6000|V100|C1|C2|C3|C4|C5|C6|C7|C8|C9|C10]\r\n                                  Machine type  [required]\r\n  --apiKey TEXT                   API key to use this time only\r\n  --help                          Show this message and exit."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":803,"aggregated":"Usage: paperspace-python machines availability [OPTIONS]\r\n\r\n  Get machine availability for the given region and machine type. Note:\r\n  availability is only provided for the dedicated GPU machine types. Also, not\r\n  all machine types are available in all regions\r\n\r\nOptions:\r\n  --region [ca1|ny2|ams1]         Name of the region  [required]\r\n  --machineType [Air|Standard|Pro|Advanced|GPU+|P4000|P5000|P6000|V100|C1|C2|C3|C4|C5|C6|C7|C8|C9|C10]\r\n                                  Machine type  [required]\r\n  --apiKey TEXT                   API key to use this time only\r\n  --help                          Show this message and exit.","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774204469652}}
{"type":"message","id":"2d626623","parentId":"73574067","timestamp":"2026-03-22T18:34:34.915Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the machine types. The available types include GPU types like P4000, P5000, P6000, V100. Let me check availability for GPU+ or V100 in ny2 (New York). But wait - Zach mentioned he has an A5000 on Paperspace Gradient, so maybe I should check what machine types are available for GPU compute.Actually, let me look at the create command to understand what options are available.","thinkingSignature":"833435746608adbe047fd8a3702cfa3189db69f186b0fc44766cf02f0a7d9db0"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_x4zkdyiipgqy_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"& \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\Python\\Python312\\Scripts\\paperspace-python.exe\" machines create --help 2>&1","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":34612,"output":159,"cacheRead":12352,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":47123,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774204469658}}
{"type":"message","id":"3986545d","parentId":"2d626623","timestamp":"2026-03-22T18:34:35.756Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_x4zkdyiipgqy_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Usage: paperspace-python machines create [OPTIONS]\r\n\r\n  Create a new Paperspace virtual machine. If you are using an individual\r\n  account, you will be assigned as the owner of the machine. If you are a team\r\n  administrator, you must specify the user that should be assigned to the\r\n  machine, either by specifing a user id, or by providing an email address,\r\n  password, first name and last name for the creation of a new user on the\r\n  team.\r\n\r\nOptions:\r\n  --region [ca1|ny2|ams1]         Name of the region  [required]\r\n  --machineType [Air|Standard|Pro|Advanced|GPU+|P4000|P5000|P6000|V100|C1|C2|C3|C4|C5|C6|C7|C8|C9|C10]\r\n                                  Machine type  [required]\r\n  --size INTEGER                  Storage size for the machine in GB\r\n                                  [required]\r\n  --billingType [hourly|monthly]  Either 'monthly' or 'hourly' billing\r\n                                  [required]\r\n  --machineName TEXT              A memorable name for this machine\r\n                                  [required]\r\n  --templateId TEXT               Template id of the template to use for\r\n                                  creating this machine  [required]\r\n  --assignPublicIp                Assign a new public ip address on machine\r\n                                  creation. Cannot be used with\r\n                                  dynamicPublicIp\r\n  --dynamicPublicIp               Assigns a new public ip address on machine\r\n                                  start and releases it from the account on\r\n                                  machine stop. Cannot be used with\r\n                                  assignPublicIp\r\n  --networkId TEXT                If creating on a specific network, specify\r\n                                  its id\r\n  --teamId TEXT                   If creating the machine for a team, specify\r\n                                  the team id\r\n  --userId TEXT                   If assigning to an existing user other than\r\n                                  yourself, specify the user id (mutually\r\n                                  exclusive with email, password, firstName,\r\n                                  lastName)\r\n  --email TEXT                    If creating a new user for this machine,\r\n                                  specify their email address (mutually\r\n                                  exclusive with userId)\r\n  --password TEXT                 If creating a new user, specify their\r\n                                  password (mutually exclusive with userId)\r\n  --firstName TEXT                If creating a new user, specify their first\r\n                                  name (mutually exclusive with userId)\r\n  --lastName TEXT                 If creating a new user, specify their last\r\n                                  name (mutually exclusive with userId)\r\n  --notificationEmail TEXT        Send a notification to this email address\r\n                                  when complete\r\n  --scriptId TEXT                 The script id of a script to be run on\r\n                                  startup. See the Script Guide for more info\r\n                                  on using scripts\r\n  --apiKey TEXT                   API key to use this time only\r\n  --help                          Show this message and exit."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":826,"aggregated":"Usage: paperspace-python machines create [OPTIONS]\r\n\r\n  Create a new Paperspace virtual machine. If you are using an individual\r\n  account, you will be assigned as the owner of the machine. If you are a team\r\n  administrator, you must specify the user that should be assigned to the\r\n  machine, either by specifing a user id, or by providing an email address,\r\n  password, first name and last name for the creation of a new user on the\r\n  team.\r\n\r\nOptions:\r\n  --region [ca1|ny2|ams1]         Name of the region  [required]\r\n  --machineType [Air|Standard|Pro|Advanced|GPU+|P4000|P5000|P6000|V100|C1|C2|C3|C4|C5|C6|C7|C8|C9|C10]\r\n                                  Machine type  [required]\r\n  --size INTEGER                  Storage size for the machine in GB\r\n                                  [required]\r\n  --billingType [hourly|monthly]  Either 'monthly' or 'hourly' billing\r\n                                  [required]\r\n  --machineName TEXT              A memorable name for this machine\r\n                                  [required]\r\n  --templateId TEXT               Template id of the template to use for\r\n                                  creating this machine  [required]\r\n  --assignPublicIp                Assign a new public ip address on machine\r\n                                  creation. Cannot be used with\r\n                                  dynamicPublicIp\r\n  --dynamicPublicIp               Assigns a new public ip address on machine\r\n                                  start and releases it from the account on\r\n                                  machine stop. Cannot be used with\r\n                                  assignPublicIp\r\n  --networkId TEXT                If creating on a specific network, specify\r\n                                  its id\r\n  --teamId TEXT                   If creating the machine for a team, specify\r\n                                  the team id\r\n  --userId TEXT                   If assigning to an existing user other than\r\n                                  yourself, specify the user id (mutually\r\n                                  exclusive with email, password, firstName,\r\n                                  lastName)\r\n  --email TEXT                    If creating a new user for this machine,\r\n                                  specify their email address (mutually\r\n                                  exclusive with userId)\r\n  --password TEXT                 If creating a new user, specify their\r\n                                  password (mutually exclusive with userId)\r\n  --firstName TEXT                If creating a new user, specify their first\r\n                                  name (mutually exclusive with userId)\r\n  --lastName TEXT                 If creating a new user, specify their last\r\n                                  name (mutually exclusive with userId)\r\n  --notificationEmail TEXT        Send a notification to this email address\r\n                                  when complete\r\n  --scriptId TEXT                 The script id of a script to be run on\r\n                                  startup. See the Script Guide for more info\r\n                                  on using scripts\r\n  --apiKey TEXT                   API key to use this time only\r\n  --help                          Show this message and exit.","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774204475752}}
