{"type":"message","id":"edd601d1","parentId":"d1a37b47","timestamp":"2026-03-22T18:37:28.404Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No Ollama in WSL either. Let me try to install it in WSL.Actually, wait. Zach explicitly said no Ollama. Let me re-read the TOOLS.md:\n\n\"**Note:** Zach said no Ollama — sandbox uses stateless compositional architecture instead\"\n\nSo Ollama is off the table. Zach specifically rejected it.Let me try a different approach. Let me set up the Paperspace job properly with vLLM and see if I can get it working. The key issue before was the bucket credentials when creating a job with local workspace. Using `--workspaceUrl` to clone from git should work.Let me try creating a job that:\n1. Uses the vLLM container\n2. Clones a setup script from a git repo\n3. Runs vLLM with the Qwen model\n4. Exposes port 8000Actually, let me think about this more carefully. For the Paperspace job to be useful as an API endpoint, I'd need:\n1. The job to keep running (not exit immediately)\n2. A public IP/URL to access it\n3. The vLLM server running on port 8000Let me create a proper job spec. I'll use a GitHub repo with a startup script and run it on Paperspace.","thinkingSignature":"b10fa8183ac26033804f87870364bf6a491831cfb12f7f9afd36e2bd73bba2cc"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_52yjcrhlfst1_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"#!/bin/bash\n# Nova Gateway startup script for Paperspace\n\nset -e\n\necho \"=== Nova Gateway Starting ===\"\necho \"Starting vLLM with Qwen3.5-35B...\"\n\n# The model we'll use\nMODEL=\"HauhauCS/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive\"\n\n# Start vLLM\npython -m vllm.entrypoints.openai.api_server \\\n  --model $MODEL \\\n  --tensor-parallel-size 1 \\\n  --host 0.0.0.0 \\\n  --port 8000 \\\n  --gpu-memory-utilization 0.90 \\\n  --max-model-len 8192 \\\n  --enforce-eager \\\n  2>&1 &\n\nVLLM_PID=$!\necho \"vLLM started with PID: $VLLM_PID\"\n\n# Wait for server to be ready\necho \"Waiting for vLLM server to be ready...\"\nfor i in {1..60}; do\n  if curl -s http://localhost:8000/v1/models > /dev/null 2>&1; then\n    echo \"vLLM server is ready!\"\n    exit 0\n  fi\n  sleep 5\n  echo \"Waiting... ($i/60)\"\ndone\n\necho \"Warning: vLLM server may not be fully ready, but process is running\"\nexit 0\n","file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\nova-gateway\\start.sh"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":49329,"output":612,"cacheRead":12352,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62293,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774204630993}}
