{"type":"message","id":"d1fb81c7","parentId":"813b68f4","timestamp":"2026-03-22T19:47:02.553Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me check the job logs for the pending job to see if there's any more information. Maybe the container is downloading and that's why it's slow.Actually, let me try a completely different approach. Let me use a smaller model first to test if the infrastructure works, then scale up. Or let me try using Lambda Labs or another cloud GPU provider since Paperspace seems to have resource issues.Lambda Labs has RTX 3060s at $0.50/hr - not as good as A5000 but might be more available. But they also require Docker runtime which I can't use on Windows without WSL2 properly configured.Actually, let me try a different approach - use the `run` command which is designed for one-off script execution. \n\nI think the real issue might be that my jobs are timing out before the container even downloads - the first job showed \"Couldn't retrieve bucket credentials\" which suggests the workspace upload failed, and that might be blocking the job from starting properly even though it was created. Let me try running a simpler command first to verify the infrastructure works.","thinkingSignature":"84e352abac3c0e2fa2082cebf80aa5abb4ffce7398575b0a4c367b0390263302"},{"type":"text","text":"Paperspace GPU+ cluster seems to have no available machines right now — keeps stalling at Pending. Let me test with a simple container to confirm the infrastructure works:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_mhw5d60e2t7e_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"& \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\Python\\Python312\\Scripts\\paperspace-python.exe\" jobs create --name \"nova-ping-test\" --container \"alpine:latest\" --machineType \"GPU+\" --command \"ping -c 3 google.com\" --projectId \"pdz19rnk164\" 2>&1","timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":57087,"outp