{"type":"message","id":"d9cfa3a4","parentId":"def382a6","timestamp":"2026-03-22T19:47:19.346Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The ping test job is also Pending. And both vLLM jobs are also Pending. This is definitely a Paperspace GPU shortage issue. The \"Couldn't retrieve bucket credentials\" message seems to be a warning but the jobs are still being created.\n\nLet me try a different approach - maybe there's a way to use a different cluster or machine type. Or maybe I should try Lambda Labs instead.\n\nActually, let me look at this from a different angle. Zach wanted me to be independent and get things done. Paperspace GPU+ cluster seems to be full/oversubscribed. Let me:\n\n1. Try a different machine type on Paperspace (maybe P5000 or V100)\n\n\n2. Check if there's a reserved capacity option\n3. Consider Lambda Labs as a fallback\n\nThe real issue is that Paperspace Gradient's GPU+ cluster is likely oversubscribed with long queue times. I could pivot to Lambda Labs, but their Docker runtime requirement makes it impractical on Windows. Let me try accessing the job logs directly via the API to understand what's happening - maybe I can reach the instance even while it's pending.","thinkingSignature":"23d0f6a5de61962dbe6665cbd0a8411cf16f4718754073d78622f486f44d52af"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_n3vclboho1bo_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"$headers = @{ \"X-API-Key\" = \"131e4cbc99405a0e3af9710cc1607c\" }; try { Invoke-RestMethod -Uri \"https://api.paperspace.io/jobs/juj5c58kw0vouful/logs/?line=1&limit=50\" -Method GET -Headers $headers } catch { $_.Exception.Message }","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":58338,"output":344,"cacheRead":12605,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":71287,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774208831673}}
