{"type":"message","id":"0a05682b","parentId":"3b25b9b0","timestamp":"2026-03-22T19:47:40.031Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The logs endpoint isn't working either. Let me try the direct API endpoint that the paperspace-python library uses.\n\nFrom the jobs.py code: `base_url = \"/jobs/logs\"` and it uses `self.api.get(\"/jobs/logs\", params=...)`. So the endpoint would be `https://api.paperspace.io/jobs/logs?jobId=...`\n\nBut it's returning 404. Maybe the endpoint requires authentication differently, or maybe it's a different URL.\n\nLet me think about this differently. The jobs are being created but staying in \"Pending\" state. This suggests either:\n1. No GPU nodes available in the cluster\n2. The job is queued but never assigned a node\n\n\n3. Paperspace infrastructure is having issues\n\nI should check if the `PS Jobs` cluster is actually the right one, or try switching to a different cluster or machine type. I could also explore whether a CPU instance with GPU attachment would work, though that seems unlikely. The A5000 in the GPU+ tier should be capable of running Qwen3.5-35B with Q4_K_M quantization, so maybe the real problem is just resource availability. Let me try a smaller model first to see if the infrastructure itself is functional, and if that works, I can build from there.\n\nI think I should give it more time to see if it eventually starts. I also need to update the memory file since I've been working on this for a while without documenting progress.","thinkingSignature":"449233bf6f321ee4f461ac15ea2bf6dee9dba6b264e7a0c9cdbac1ef7614b177"},{"type":"text","text":"Paperspace GPU cluster seems oversubscribed — both jobs stuck on Pending. The \"bucket credentials\" warning is just about artifact storage, jobs still get created.\n\nLet me update my memory and keep monitoring while I explore alternatives:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_249n58zm6t0a_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\